"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pfo1665702636052.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pfo1665702636052.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pfo1665702636052.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pfo1665702636052\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Tree View\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determines whether the Tree widget includes a tree view, or only a list view.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__section_b1d_ytt_ywb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1015181e51\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__table_d12527e1_d12528e1_d12529e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dynamic? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> No </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported in Grid? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> No </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dependencies: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> No </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__section_hhk_ztt_ywb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1015181e97\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__p_d105263e1_d105264e1_d105265e1\">The tree widget must have a view specified. If you do\n        not specify a view, the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Tree View</span> is enabled.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__p_d105266e1_d105267e1_d105268e1\">If both <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Tree View</span> and\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">List View</span> are enabled, the tree widget is displayed with two panes\n        separated by a split bar. The left pane contains the hierarchical tree structure, the right\n        contains the nodes and leaves of the selected tree item. The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">List\n          View</span> displays both nodes and leaves. Double-clicking a node displays its\n        leaves.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__p_d105269e1_d105270e1_d105271e1\">If you do not enable the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">List\n          View</span> when defining the initial tree widget properties, you cannot dynamically\n        show or hide the list view at run time.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__note_lvk_15t_ywb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">List View</span> check box in the\n        Properties Inspector is not the same as the ListView property in ProcScript, which maps to\n          <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qlx1665702636554.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qlx1665702636554.html\" title=\"Format of data is displayed in the List View.\">List View Style (ListView)</a>.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pfo1665702636052__section_v1v_j5t_ywb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1015181e140\">Applies To</h2>\n<p class=\"p\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gge1665702634237.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gge1665702634237.html\" title=\"The utree widget enables users to view and navigate structured data as a hierarchy. Uniface provides a logical widget called Tree, which is mapped to utree.\">utree (Tree)</a></p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kpu1665702635984.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Tree View and List View</a><p>Indicate the views displayed in the tree widget.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615174\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615174\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Tree View Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Tree View Determines whether the Tree widget includes a tree view, or only a list view. Usage Dynamic? No Supported in Grid? No Dependencies: No Description The tree widget must have a view specified. If you do not specify a view, the Tree View is enabled. If both Tree View and List View are enabled, the tree widget is displayed with two panes separated by a split bar. The left pane contains the hierarchical tree structure, the right contains the nodes and leaves of the selected tree item. The List View displays both nodes and leaves. Double-clicking a node displays its leaves. If you do not enable the List View when defining the initial tree widget properties, you cannot dynamically show or hide the list view at run time. Note: The List View check box in the Properties Inspector is not the same as the ListView property in ProcScript, which maps to List View Style (ListView) . Applies To utree (Tree) Related Links Tree View and List View Indicate the views displayed in the tree widget. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}